Syntax: chiblock

Channels chi energy into a defensive barrier that improves your armor class
during combat. Unlike the finisher-based shieldblock, chiblock draws directly
from your chi reserves and can be used independently of combo state.

Effects when activated:
  - Applies a -1 AC (armor class) bonus for (combo_count - 3) combat rounds.
  - Activates a 10-round cooldown preventing reuse.
  - Skill proficiency improves on successful use.

The chi cost increases if used while the cooldown is active. The lower your
armor class number, the harder you are to hit.

Requirements:
  - Must be in combat.
  - Must have chi available (cost varies with cooldown).
  - Must have the Chiblock skill learned.

See also: shelp chiblock shieldblock chakra dodge parry
